               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-746" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-746" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-746" type="surname" value="MOORISH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-746" type="given" value="MARTHA"></interp>MARTHA MOORISH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Thomas Moorish, of Gray's-inn-lane: we keep a general shop. On the 25th of May I left the shop for about a minute, and saw the prisoner drawing his arm across the counter, and leaving the shop—he had pulled out the till, and taken out a cocoa<lb></lb>nut shell, which had two shillings and four sixpences in it—I went after him—he was taken by an officer, and the money taken out of his pocket at the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-747" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-747" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-747" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-747" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HUNT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 66.) I was called on by the prose<lb></lb>cutrix to take the prisoner—I found him in a necessary, down a back place which is no thoroughfare—I searched him, and found two shillings and four sixpences in his left-hand waistcoat pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-748" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-748" type="surname" value="MEAL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-748" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MEAL</persName>
                  </hi>. I picked up this cocoa nut-shell about a yard from where the prisoner was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I belong to North Shields—I came up by the brig—I had occasion to go to that place—the officer came and took me—I asked the prosecutrix what she had lost—she said, "Between four and five shil<lb></lb>lings, from the till"—when they took me to the station-house, I pulled my money out—she then said it was two shillings and four sixpences.</p>
